okens (classic) need the `admin:read` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"interactions/get-restrictions-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/interaction-limits\",\n      \"tag\": \"interactions\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get interaction restrictions for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Shows which type of GitHub user can interact with this organization and when the restriction expires. If there is no restrictions, you will see an empty response.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"interactions/set-restrictions-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/interaction-limits\",\n      \"tag\": \"interactions\",\n      \"summary\": \"Set interaction restrictions for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Temporarily restricts interactions to a certain type of GitHub user in any public repository in the given organization. You must be an organization owner to set these restrictions. Setting the interaction limit at the organization level will overwrite any interaction limits that are set for individual repositories owned by the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"interactions/remove-restrictions-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/interaction-limits\",\n      \"tag\": \"interactions\",\n      \"summary\": \"Remove interaction restrictions for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Removes all interaction restrictions from public repositories in the given organization. You must be an organization owner to remove restrictions.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-pending-invitations\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/invitations\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List pending organization invitations\",\n      \"description\": \"The return hash contains a `role` field which refers to the Organization\\nInvitation role and will be one of the following values: `direct_member`, `admin`,\\n`billing_manager`, or `hiring_manager`. If the invitee is not a GitHub\\nmember, the `login` field in the return hash will be `null`.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"role\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Filter invitations by their member role.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"invitation_source\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Filter invitations by their invitation source.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\",\n          \"role\",\n          \"invitation_source\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/create-invitation\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/invitations\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create an organization invitation\",\n      \"description\": \"Invite people to an organization by using their GitHub user ID or their email address. In order to create invitations in an organization, the authenticated user must be an organization owner.\\n\\nThis endpoint triggers [notifications](https://docs.github.com/github/managing-subscriptions-and-notifications-on-github/about-notifications). Creating content too quickly using this endpoint may result in secondary rate limiting. For more information, see \\\"[Rate limits for the API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/rate-limits-for-the-rest-api#about-secondary-rate-limits)\\\"\\nand \\\"[Best practices for using the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/best-practices-for-using-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"201\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/cancel-invitation\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/invitations/{invitation_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Cancel an organization invitation\",\n      \"description\": \"Cancel an organization invitation. In order to cancel an organization invitation, the authenticated user must be an organization owner.\\n\\nThis endpoint triggers [notifications](https://docs.github.com/github/managing-subscriptions-and-notifications-on-github/about-notifications).\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"invitation_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the invitation.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"invitation_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-invitation-teams\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/invitations/{invitation_id}/teams\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization invitation teams\",\n      \"description\": \"List all teams associated with an invitation. In order to see invitations in an organization, the authenticated user must be an organization owner.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"invitation_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the invitation.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"invitation_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-issue-fields\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-fields\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List issue fields for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists all issue fields for an organization. OAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the read:org scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/create-issue-field\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-fields\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create issue field for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Creates a new issue field for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue fields in [Managing issue fields in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/using-issues/managing-issue-fields-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/update-issue-field\",\n      \"method\": \"PATCH\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-fields/{issue_field_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Update issue field for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Updates an issue field for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue fields in [Managing issue fields in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/using-issues/managing-issue-fields-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue_field_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the issue field.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"issue_field_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/delete-issue-field\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-fields/{issue_field_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Delete issue field for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Deletes an issue field for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue fields in [Managing issue fields in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/using-issues/managing-issue-fields-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue_field_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the issue field.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"issue_field_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-issue-types\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-types\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List issue types for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists all issue types for an organization. OAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the read:org scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/create-issue-type\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-types\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create issue type for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Create a new issue type for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue types in [Managing issue types in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/configuring-issues/managing-issue-types-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/update-issue-type\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-types/{issue_type_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Update issue type for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Updates an issue type for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue types in [Managing issue types in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/configuring-issues/managing-issue-types-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue_type_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the issue type.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"issue_type_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/delete-issue-type\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issue-types/{issue_type_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Delete issue type for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Deletes an issue type for an organization.\\n\\nYou can find out more about issue types in [Managing issue types in an organization](https://docs.github.com/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/configuring-issues/managing-issue-types-in-an-organization).\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be an administrator for the organization. OAuth app tokens and\\npersonal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue_type_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the issue type.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"issue_type_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"issues/list-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/issues\",\n      \"tag\": \"issues\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization issues assigned to the authenticated user\",\n      \"description\": \"List issues in an organization assigned to the authenticated user.\\n\\n\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e GitHub's REST API considers every pull request an issue, but not every issue is a pull request. For this reason, \\\"Issues\\\" endpoints may return both issues and pull requests in the response. You can identify pull requests by the `pull_request` key. Be aware that the `id` of a pull request returned from \\\"Issues\\\" endpoints will be an _issue id_. To find out the pull request id, use the \\\"[List pull requests](https://docs.github.com/rest/pulls/pulls#list-pull-requests)\\\" endpoint.\\n\\nThis endpoint supports the following custom media types. For more information, see \\\"[Media types](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/getting-started-with-the-rest-api#media-types).\\\"\\n\\n- **`application/vnd.github.raw+json`**: Returns the raw markdown body. Response will include `body`. This is the default if you do not pass any specific media type.\\n- **`application/vnd.github.text+json`**: Returns a text only representation of the markdown body. Response will include `body_text`.\\n- **`application/vnd.github.html+json`**: Returns HTML rendered from the body's markdown. Response will include `body_html`.\\n- **`application/vnd.github.full+json`**: Returns raw, text, and HTML representations. Response will include `body`, `body_text`, and `body_html`.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"filter\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Indicates which sorts of issues to return. `assigned` means issues assigned to you. `created` means issues created by you. `mentioned` means issues mentioning you. `subscribed` means issues you're subscribed to updates for. `all` or `repos` means all issues you can see, regardless of participation or creation.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"state\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Indicates the state of the issues to return.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"labels\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A list of comma separated label names. Example: `bug,ui,@high`\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"type\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Can be the name of an issue type.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"What to sort results by.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"direction\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The direction to sort the results by.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"since\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Only show results that were last updated after the given time. This is a timestamp in [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) format: `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ`.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"filter\",\n          \"state\",\n          \"labels\",\n          \"type\",\n          \"sort\",\n          \"direction\",\n          \"since\",\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-members\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization members\",\n      \"description\": \"List all users who are members of an organization. If the authenticated user is also a member of this organization then both concealed and public members will be returned.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"filter\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Filter members returned in the list. `2fa_disabled` means that only members without [two-factor authentication](https://github.com/blog/1614-two-factor-authentication) enabled will be returned. `2fa_insecure` means that only members with [insecure 2FA methods](https://docs.github.com/organizations/keeping-your-organization-secure/managing-two-factor-authentication-for-your-organization/requiring-two-factor-authentication-in-your-organization#requiring-secure-methods-of-two-factor-authentication-in-your-organization) will be returned. These options are only available for organization owners.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"role\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Filter members returned by their role.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"filter\",\n          \"role\",\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/check-membership-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Check organization membership for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"Check if a user is, publicly or privately, a member of the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"302\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/remove-member\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Remove an organization member\",\n      \"description\": \"Removing a user from this list will remove them from all teams and they will no longer have any access to the organization's repositories.\\n\\n\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e If a user has both direct membership in the organization as well as indirect membership via an enterprise team, only their direct membership will be removed. Their indirect membership via an enterprise team remains until the user is removed from the enterprise team.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"403\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"codespaces/get-codespaces-for-user-in-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}/codespaces\",\n      \"tag\": \"codespaces\",\n      \"summary\": \"List codespaces for a user in organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists the codespaces that a member of an organization has for repositories in that organization.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"304\",\n        \"401\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"codespaces/delete-from-organization\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}/codespaces/{codespace_name}\",\n      \"tag\": \"codespaces\",\n      \"summary\": \"Delete a codespace from the organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Deletes a user's codespace.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"codespace_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The name of the codespace.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"202\",\n        \"304\",\n        \"401\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\",\n          \"codespace_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"codespaces/stop-in-organization\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}/codespaces/{codespace_name}/stop\",\n      \"tag\": \"codespaces\",\n      \"summary\": \"Stop a codespace for an organization user\",\n      \"description\": \"Stops a user's codespace.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"codespace_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The name of the codespace.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"304\",\n        \"401\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\",\n          \"codespace_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"copilot/get-copilot-seat-details-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/members/{username}/copilot\",\n      \"tag\": \"copilot\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get Copilot seat assignment details for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e This endpoint is in public preview and is subject to change.\\n\\nGets the GitHub Copilot seat details for a member of an organization who currently has access to GitHub Copilot.\\n\\nThe seat object contains information about the user's most recent Copilot activity. Users must have telemetry enabled in their IDE for Copilot in the IDE activity to be reflected in `last_activity_at`.\\nFor more information about activity data, see [Metrics data properties for GitHub Copilot](https://docs.github.com/copilot/reference/metrics-data).\\n\\nOnly organization owners can view Copilot seat assignment details for members of their organization.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need either the `manage_billing:copilot` or `read:org` scopes to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"401\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/get-membership-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/memberships/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get organization membership for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"In order to get a user's membership with an organization, the authenticated user must be an organization member. The `state` parameter in the response can be used to identify the user's membership status.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/set-membership-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/memberships/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Set organization membership for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"Only authenticated organization owners can add a member to the organization or update the member's role.\\n\\n*   If the authenticated user is _adding_ a member to the organization, the invited user will receive an email inviting them to the organization. The user's [membership status](https://docs.github.com/rest/orgs/members#get-organization-membership-for-a-user) will be `pending` until they accept the invitation.\\n    \\n*   Authenticated users can _update_ a user's membership by passing the `role` parameter. If the authenticated user changes a member's role to `admin`, the affected user will receive an email notifying them that they've been made an organization owner. If the authenticated user changes an owner's role to `member`, no email will be sent.\\n\\n**Rate limits**\\n\\nTo prevent abuse, organization owners are limited to creating 50 organization invitations for an organization within a 24 hour period. If the organization is more than one month old or on a paid plan, the limit is 500 invitations per 24 hour period.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/remove-membership-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/memberships/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Remove organization membership for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"In order to remove a user's membership with an organization, the authenticated user must be an organization owner.\\n\\nIf the specified user is an active member of the organization, this will remove them from the organization. If the specified user has been invited to the organization, this will cancel their invitation. The specified user will receive an email notification in both cases.\\n\\n\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e If a user has both direct membership in the organization as well as indirect membership via an enterprise team, only their direct membership will be removed. Their indirect membership via an enterprise team remains until the user is removed from the enterprise team.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/list-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization migrations\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists the most recent migrations, including both exports (which can be started through the REST API) and imports (which cannot be started using the REST API).\\n\\nA list of `repositories` is only returned for export migrations.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"exclude\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Exclude attributes from the API response to improve performance\",\n          \"type\": \"array\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\",\n          \"exclude\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/start-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"Start an organization migration\",\n      \"description\": \"Initiates the generation of a migration archive.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"201\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/get-status-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations/{migration_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get an organization migration status\",\n      \"description\": \"Fetches the status of a migration.\\n\\nThe `state` of a migration can be one of the following values:\\n\\n*   `pending`, which means the migration hasn't started yet.\\n*   `exporting`, which means the migration is in progress.\\n*   `exported`, which means the migration finished successfully.\\n*   `failed`, which means the migration failed.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"migration_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the migration.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"exclude\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Exclude attributes from the API response to improve performance\",\n          \"type\": \"array\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"migration_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"exclude\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/download-archive-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations/{migration_id}/archive\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"Download an organization migration archive\",\n      \"description\": \"Fetches the URL to a migration archive.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"migration_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the migration.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"302\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"migration_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/delete-archive-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations/{migration_id}/archive\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"Delete an organization migration archive\",\n      \"description\": \"Deletes a previous migration archive. Migration archives are automatically deleted after seven days.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"migration_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the migration.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"migration_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/unlock-repo-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations/{migration_id}/repos/{repo_name}/lock\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"Unlock an organization repository\",\n      \"description\": \"Unlocks a repository that was locked for migration. You should unlock each migrated repository and [delete them](https://docs.github.com/rest/repos/repos#delete-a-repository) when the migration is complete and you no longer need the source data.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"migration_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the migration.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"repo_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"repo_name parameter\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"migration_id\",\n          \"repo_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrations/list-repos-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/migrations/{migration_id}/repositories\",\n      \"tag\": \"migrations\",\n      \"summary\": \"List repositories in an organization migration\",\n      \"description\": \"List all the repositories for this organization migration.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"migration_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the migration.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"migration_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-org-roles\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/organization-roles\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get all organization roles for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists the organization roles available in this organization. For more information on organization roles, see \\\"[Using organization roles](https://docs.github.com/organizations/managing-peoples-access-to-your-organization-with-roles/using-organization-roles).\\\"\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be one of:\\n\\n- An administrator for the organization.\\n- An organization member (or a member of a team) assigned a custom organization role that includes the **View organization roles** (`read_organization_custom_org_role`) permission. For more information, see \\\"[Permissions for organization access](https://docs.github.com/organizations/managing-peoples-access-to-your-organization-with-roles/permissions-of-custom-organization-roles#permissions-for-organization-access).\\\"\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `admin:org` scope to use this endpoint.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n  