ase sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"view_number\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The number that identifies the project view.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"fields\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Limit results to specific fields, by their IDs. If not specified, the\\ntitle field will be returned.\\n\\nExample: `fields[]=123\u0026fields[]=456\u0026fields[]=789` or `fields=123,456,789`\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"before\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A cursor, as given in the [Link header](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api#using-link-headers). If specified, the query only searches for results before this cursor. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"after\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A cursor, as given in the [Link header](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api#using-link-headers). If specified, the query only searches for results after this cursor. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"304\",\n        \"401\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"project_number\",\n          \"org\",\n          \"view_number\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"fields\",\n          \"before\",\n          \"after\",\n          \"per_page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-get-organization-definitions\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/schema\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get all custom properties for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Gets all custom properties defined for an organization.\\nOrganization members can read these properties.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-create-or-update-organization-definitions\",\n      \"method\": \"PATCH\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/schema\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create or update custom properties for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Creates new or updates existing custom properties defined for an organization in a batch.\\n\\nIf the property already exists, the existing property will be replaced with the new values.\\nMissing optional values will fall back to default values, previous values will be overwritten.\\nE.g. if a property exists with `values_editable_by: org_and_repo_actors` and it's updated without specifying `values_editable_by`, it will be updated to default value `org_actors`.\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be one of:\\n  - An administrator for the organization.\\n  - A user, or a user on a team, with the fine-grained permission of `custom_properties_org_definitions_manager` in the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-get-organization-definition\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/schema/{custom_property_name}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get a custom property for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Gets a custom property that is defined for an organization.\\nOrganization members can read these properties.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"custom_property_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The custom property name\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"custom_property_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-create-or-update-organization-definition\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/schema/{custom_property_name}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create or update a custom property for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Creates a new or updates an existing custom property that is defined for an organization.\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be one of:\\n- An administrator for the organization.\\n- A user, or a user on a team, with the fine-grained permission of `custom_properties_org_definitions_manager` in the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"custom_property_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The custom property name\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"custom_property_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-delete-organization-definition\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/schema/{custom_property_name}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Remove a custom property for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Removes a custom property that is defined for an organization.\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be one of:\\n  - An administrator for the organization.\\n  - A user, or a user on a team, with the fine-grained permission of `custom_properties_org_definitions_manager` in the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"custom_property_name\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The custom property name\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"custom_property_name\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-get-organization-values\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/values\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List custom property values for organization repositories\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists organization repositories with all of their custom property values.\\nOrganization members can read these properties.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"repository_query\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Finds repositories in the organization with a query containing one or more search keywords and qualifiers. Qualifiers allow you to limit your search to specific areas of GitHub. The REST API supports the same qualifiers as the web interface for GitHub. To learn more about the format of the query, see [Constructing a search query](https://docs.github.com/rest/search/search#constructing-a-search-query). See \\\"[Searching for repositories](https://docs.github.com/articles/searching-for-repositories/)\\\" for a detailed list of qualifiers.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\",\n          \"repository_query\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/custom-properties-for-repos-create-or-update-organization-values\",\n      \"method\": \"PATCH\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/properties/values\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create or update custom property values for organization repositories\",\n      \"description\": \"Create new or update existing custom property values for repositories in a batch that belong to an organization.\\nEach target repository will have its custom property values updated to match the values provided in the request.\\n\\nA maximum of 30 repositories can be updated in a single request.\\n\\nUsing a value of `null` for a custom property will remove or 'unset' the property value from the repository.\\n\\nTo use this endpoint, the authenticated user must be one of:\\n  - An administrator for the organization.\\n  - A user, or a user on a team, with the fine-grained permission of `custom_properties_org_values_editor` in the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/list-public-members\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/public_members\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"List public organization members\",\n      \"description\": \"Members of an organization can choose to have their membership publicized or not.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/check-public-membership-for-user\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/public_members/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Check public organization membership for a user\",\n      \"description\": \"Check if the provided user is a public member of the organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/set-public-membership-for-authenticated-user\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/public_members/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Set public organization membership for the authenticated user\",\n      \"description\": \"The user can publicize their own membership. (A user cannot publicize the membership for another user.)\\n\\nNote that you'll need to set `Content-Length` to zero when calling out to this endpoint. For more information, see \\\"[HTTP method](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/getting-started-with-the-rest-api#http-method).\\\"\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"403\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/remove-public-membership-for-authenticated-user\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/public_members/{username}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Remove public organization membership for the authenticated user\",\n      \"description\": \"Removes the public membership for the authenticated user from the specified organization, unless public visibility is enforced by default.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"username\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/list-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/repos\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization repositories\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists repositories for the specified organization.\\n\\n\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e In order to see the `security_and_analysis` block for a repository you must have admin permissions for the repository or be an owner or security manager for the organization that owns the repository. For more information, see \\\"[Managing security managers in your organization](https://docs.github.com/organizations/managing-peoples-access-to-your-organization-with-roles/managing-security-managers-in-your-organization).\\\"\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"type\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Specifies the types of repositories you want returned.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The property to sort the results by.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"direction\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The order to sort by. Default: `asc` when using `full_name`, otherwise `desc`.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"type\",\n          \"sort\",\n          \"direction\",\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/create-in-org\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/repos\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create an organization repository\",\n      \"description\": \"Creates a new repository in the specified organization. The authenticated user must be a member of the organization.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `public_repo` or `repo` scope to create a public repository, and `repo` scope to create a private repository.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"201\",\n        \"403\",\n        \"422\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/get-org-rulesets\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get all organization repository rulesets\",\n      \"description\": \"Get all the repository rulesets for an organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"targets\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of rule targets to filter by.\\nIf provided, only rulesets that apply to the specified targets will be returned.\\nFor example, `branch,tag,push`.\\n\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\",\n          \"targets\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/create-org-ruleset\",\n      \"method\": \"POST\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Create an organization repository ruleset\",\n      \"description\": \"Create a repository ruleset for an organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"201\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/get-org-rule-suites\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/rule-suites\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"List organization rule suites\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists suites of rule evaluations at the organization level.\\nFor more information, see \\\"[Managing rulesets for repositories in your organization](https://docs.github.com/organizations/managing-organization-settings/managing-rulesets-for-repositories-in-your-organization#viewing-insights-for-rulesets).\\\"\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ref\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The name of the ref. Cannot contain wildcard characters. Optionally prefix with `refs/heads/` to limit to branches or `refs/tags/` to limit to tags. Omit the prefix to search across all refs. When specified, only rule evaluations triggered for this ref will be returned.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"repository_name\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The name of the repository to filter on.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_period\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The time period to filter by.\\n\\nFor example, `day` will filter for rule suites that occurred in the past 24 hours, and `week` will filter for rule suites that occurred in the past 7 days (168 hours).\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"actor_name\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The handle for the GitHub user account to filter on. When specified, only rule evaluations triggered by this actor will be returned.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"rule_suite_result\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The rule suite results to filter on. When specified, only suites with this result will be returned.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"ref\",\n          \"repository_name\",\n          \"time_period\",\n          \"actor_name\",\n          \"rule_suite_result\",\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/get-org-rule-suite\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/rule-suites/{rule_suite_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get an organization rule suite\",\n      \"description\": \"Gets information about a suite of rule evaluations from within an organization.\\nFor more information, see \\\"[Managing rulesets for repositories in your organization](https://docs.github.com/organizations/managing-organization-settings/managing-rulesets-for-repositories-in-your-organization#viewing-insights-for-rulesets).\\\"\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"rule_suite_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The unique identifier of the rule suite result.\\nTo get this ID, you can use [GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/rulesets/rule-suites](https://docs.github.com/rest/repos/rule-suites#list-repository-rule-suites)\\nfor repositories and [GET /orgs/{org}/rulesets/rule-suites](https://docs.github.com/rest/orgs/rule-suites#list-organization-rule-suites)\\nfor organizations.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"rule_suite_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/get-org-ruleset\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/{ruleset_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get an organization repository ruleset\",\n      \"description\": \"Get a repository ruleset for an organization.\\n\\n**Note:** To prevent leaking sensitive information, the `bypass_actors` property is only returned if the user\\nmaking the API request has write access to the ruleset.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the ruleset.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"ruleset_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/update-org-ruleset\",\n      \"method\": \"PUT\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/{ruleset_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Update an organization repository ruleset\",\n      \"description\": \"Update a ruleset for an organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the ruleset.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": true,\n      \"risk\": \"write\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"422\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"ruleset_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": true\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"repos/delete-org-ruleset\",\n      \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/{ruleset_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"repos\",\n      \"summary\": \"Delete an organization repository ruleset\",\n      \"description\": \"Delete a ruleset for an organization.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the ruleset.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"destructive\",\n      \"cacheable\": false,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"204\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"ruleset_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/get-org-ruleset-history\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/{ruleset_id}/history\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get organization ruleset history\",\n      \"description\": \"Get the history of an organization ruleset.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the ruleset.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"ruleset_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [\n          \"per_page\",\n          \"page\"\n        ],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"orgs/get-org-ruleset-version\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/rulesets/{ruleset_id}/history/{version_id}\",\n      \"tag\": \"orgs\",\n      \"summary\": \"Get organization ruleset version\",\n      \"description\": \"Get a version of an organization ruleset.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the ruleset.\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"version_id\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The ID of the version\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"hasRequestBody\": false,\n      \"risk\": \"read\",\n      \"cacheable\": true,\n      \"responseCodes\": [\n        \"200\",\n        \"404\",\n        \"500\"\n      ],\n      \"inputHints\": {\n        \"path\": [\n          \"org\",\n          \"ruleset_id\",\n          \"version_id\"\n        ],\n        \"query\": [],\n        \"headers\": [],\n        \"body\": false\n      },\n      \"graphql\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"secret-scanning/list-alerts-for-org\",\n      \"method\": \"GET\",\n      \"path\": \"/orgs/{org}/secret-scanning/alerts\",\n      \"tag\": \"secret-scanning\",\n      \"summary\": \"List secret scanning alerts for an organization\",\n      \"description\": \"Lists secret scanning alerts for eligible repositories in an organization, from newest to oldest.\\n\\nThe authenticated user must be an administrator or security manager for the organization to use this endpoint.\\n\\nOAuth app tokens and personal access tokens (classic) need the `repo` or `security_events` scope to use this endpoint. If this endpoint is only used with public repositories, the token can use the `public_repo` scope instead.\",\n      \"parameters\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"org\",\n          \"in\": \"path\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": \"The organization name. The name is not case sensitive.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"state\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Set to `open` or `resolved` to only list secret scanning alerts in a specific state.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"secret_type\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of secret types to return. All default secret patterns are returned. To return generic patterns, pass the token name(s) in the parameter. See \\\"[Supported secret scanning patterns](https://docs.github.com/code-security/secret-scanning/introduction/supported-secret-scanning-patterns#supported-secrets)\\\" for a complete list of secret types.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"exclude_secret_types\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of secret types to exclude from the results. All default secret patterns are returned except those matching the specified types. Cannot be combined with the `secret_type` parameter. See \\\"[Supported secret scanning patterns](https://docs.github.com/code-security/secret-scanning/introduction/supported-secret-scanning-patterns#supported-secrets)\\\" for a complete list of secret types.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"exclude_providers\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of provider slugs to exclude from the results.\\nProvider slugs use lowercase with underscores (e.g., `github_secret_scanning`, `clojars`).\\nYou can find the provider slug in the `provider_slug` field of each alert.\\nCannot be combined with the `providers` parameter.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"providers\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of provider slugs to filter by.\\nProvider slugs use lowercase with underscores (e.g., `github_secret_scanning`, `clojars`).\\nYou can find the provider slug in the `provider_slug` field of each alert.\\nCannot be combined with the `exclude_providers` parameter.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"resolution\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of resolutions. Only secret scanning alerts with one of these resolutions are listed. Valid resolutions are `false_positive`, `wont_fix`, `revoked`, `pattern_edited`, `pattern_deleted` or `used_in_tests`.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"assignee\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"Filters alerts by assignee. Use `*` to get all assigned alerts, `none` to get all unassigned alerts, or a GitHub username to get alerts assigned to a specific user.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The property to sort the results by. `created` means when the alert was created. `updated` means when the alert was updated or resolved.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"direction\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The direction to sort the results by.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The page number of the results to fetch. For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"per_page\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"The number of results per page (max 100). For more information, see \\\"[Using pagination in the REST API](https://docs.github.com/rest/using-the-rest-api/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api).\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"before\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A cursor, as given in the [Link header](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api#using-link-headers). If specified, the query only searches for events before this cursor. To receive an initial cursor on your first request, include an empty \\\"before\\\" query string.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"after\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A cursor, as given in the [Link header](https://docs.github.com/rest/guides/using-pagination-in-the-rest-api#using-link-headers). If specified, the query only searches for events after this cursor.  To receive an initial cursor on your first request, include an empty \\\"after\\\" query string.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"validity\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A comma-separated list of validities that, when present, will return alerts that match the validities in this list. Valid options are `active`, `inactive`, and `unknown`.\",\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"is_publicly_leaked\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A boolean value representing whether or not to filter alerts by the publicly-leaked tag being present.\",\n          \"type\": \"boolean\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"is_multi_repo\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A boolean value representing whether or not to filter alerts by the multi-repo tag being present.\",\n          \"type\": \"boolean\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"hide_secret\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A boolean value representing whether or not to hide literal secrets in the results.\",\n          \"type\": \"boolean\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"is_bypassed\",\n          \"in\": \"query\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": \"A boolean value (`true` or `false`) indicating whether to filter alerts by their push protection bypass status. When set to `true`, only alerts that were created because a push protection rule was bypassed will be returned. When set to `false`, only alerts that were not caused by a push protection bypass will be retu